# Summary of experimental CRISPR data annotated with enhancer-gene predictions. Each row represents an element-gene pair tested in a CRISPR experiment. 
#
# Column descriptions:
#
# chrPerturbationTarget, startPerturbationTarget, endPerturbationTarget: hg19 coordinates of the tested element
# chrTSS, starts, endTSS: hg19 coordinates of the tested gene
# GeneSymbol: Tested gene symbol
# CellType: Cell type in which the CRISPR experiment was performed
# IncludeInModel: Boolean indicating whether to include this element-gene pair in evaluation of predictors
# Reason: Reason the element-gene pair is not included in evaluation of predictors
# Reference: Study in which the CRISPR experiment was conducted
# RNAReadoutMethod, PerturbMethod: Experimental methods used to perturb enhancer and read out effects on RNA
# EffectSize: Fraction change in gene expression upon CRISPR perturbation
# Padj: pvalue for non-zero effect size adjusted for multiple hypothesis test correction
# Significant: Boolean indicating if padj is statistically significant
# Regulated: Boolean indicating if the element-gene pair is significant and the effect size is negative (ie gene expression decreases upon perturbation of the enhancer)
# PowerAtEffectSize.0.25: Power to detect 25% changes in gene expression
# Distance: genomic distance between the element-gene pair
# Remaining Columns represent the quantitative score of each of the predictors. See methods for details
#
